The paper discusses a machine learning approach for modelling partially observable systems and using them for planning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of compressed sensing and dimensionality reduction, which are techniques commonly used in Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also discusses the computational cost associated with learning and planning, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
